CAP theories

Consistency - all nodes see data at the same time. When a write is made, all subsequent reads from any node will
have updated value.

Availability - Every request to a non-failing node, without the guarantee that it contains the most recent version
of data.

Partition Tolerance - The system continues to operate despite arbitrary message loss or failure.

Partition tolerance is a must. So the CAP is to ask consistency or availability

Example
=======

Two servers website, one server in US another in EU.

(1)UserA connects to the closest server and update names in US.
(2)This update is replicated to the EU server
(3)When userB in EU views UserA's profile. They can see the update name.

The issue happens when connection between US and EU down.
When UserB view userA's profile.
OptionA: return an error because data is not up-to-date(Consistency)
OptionB: show potentially stale data(availability)

Above is a practical CAP theory.


When to choose consistency:
===========================
Ticket Booking/E-commerce Inventory/ Financial System

(1) Running to a same set (2) available but it's empty (oversell) (3) trade at incorrect prices

When to choose availability:
============================
Social media/content platform/review sites(YELP)

(1) fine to see a late update (2) old description is fine (3) outdated info bettern than none

